## IB Gateway (LIVE — Installed & Working)

IB Gateway 10.37 runs on the **host** (not in Docker) with a headless GUI via Xvfb.

### Architecture

```
IB Gateway (host, Java, listens *:4001)
    ↑ only accepts connections from 127.0.0.1
    |
socat proxy (systemd: ib-socat.service, host, listens *:4003)
    ↑ forwards to 127.0.0.1:4001
    |
Docker containers connect to 172.18.0.1:4003
```

### Why socat is needed

IB Gateway's "Allow connections from localhost only" setting is baked into the Java runtime and ignores `TrustedIPs` in `jts.ini` for non-localhost connections. Docker containers appear as `172.18.0.x`, so they get rejected. The socat proxy accepts on port 4003 from any IP and forwards to `127.0.0.1:4001`, making the connection appear local to IB Gateway.

